Merging all the datasets

data = merge(x=cases, y=deaths)
data = merge(x=data, y=recovered)

data = left_join(data, continents, by=c("country"="country"))

data = left_join(data, population, by=c("country"="country"))

data = left_join(data, density, by=c("country"="country"))

data = left_join(data, gdp, by=c("country"="country"))

data$date = str_replace(data$date, 'X', '')

data$day = day(as.Date(data$date,"%m.%d.%y"))

data$month = month(as.Date(data$date,"%m.%d.%y"))

month_names = c("January","February","March","April","May","June","July","August","September", "October","November","December")
data$month = month_names[data$month]

data = data[data$continent!='Oceania',]

data$date = as.Date(data$date,"%m.%d.%y")

data$log_total_gdp = log10(as.numeric(as.numeric(data$gdp_per_capita) * as.numeric(data$population)))
data$log_gdp_per_capita = log10(data$gdp_per_capita)
data$log_pop_density = log10(data$pop_density)

data = subset(data, select=-c(gdp_per_capita, pop_density))

write.csv(distinct(data), 'C:/Users/sumee/Downloads/eda/final project/latest data/data.csv', row.names=FALSE)

actuals_data = data.frame()

for (i in unique(data$country)){
  temp = data[data$country==i,]
  
  # sort_key=factor(temp$month, levels=month_names)
  # temp=temp[order(sort_key),]
  
  temp = temp[order(as.Date(temp$date,"%Y-%m-%d")),]
  
  temp$cases = c(temp$cases[1],diff(temp$cases))
  temp$deaths = c(temp$deaths[1],diff(temp$deaths))
  temp$recovered = c(temp$recovered[1],diff(temp$recovered))
  
  actuals_data = rbind(actuals_data, temp)
}
actuals_df = actuals_data

america_slow = setNames(aggregate(list(america_slow$deaths), by=list(america_slow$country, america_slow$continent, america_slow$month, america_slow$log_gdp_per_capita, america_slow$population),sum), c('country','continent', 'month','log_gdp_per_capita', 'population','deaths'))
america_slow$per_capita_death = america_slow$deaths / america_slow$population
america_slow = replace(america_slow, is.na(america_slow), 0)

death_df = rbind(asia_fast, asia_slow, america_fast, america_slow, europe_fast, europe_slow, africa_fast, africa_slow)
fast_death = na.omit(rbind(asia_fast,  america_fast, europe_fast, africa_fast))
slow_death = na.omit(rbind(asia_slow,  america_slow,  europe_slow,  africa_slow))
